SR NO. 149 ENROLLED
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby direct the Department of Transportation and Development to review and study
any potential hazards with increasing activity on the Norfolk Southern Railway originating
at the Alabo Street Wharf, pursuant to R.S. 48:390 et seq.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation and
Development shall submit a written report that includes potential ways to prevent any
foreseeable harm to the community with detailed findings to the Senate Committee on
Transportation, Highways and Public Works prior to January 1, 2027.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
secretary of the Department of Transportation and Development.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
